- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network analysis and centrality metrics. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes techniques for fast computation of betweenness centrality, which is a crucial aspect of software engineering. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper deals with graph mining and proposes techniques for efficient computation of centrality metrics. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with network analysis and the importance of nodes in a network. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible category as the paper deals with graph theory and proposes techniques for efficient computation of centrality metrics.
